## §A.4 Falsifier preregister

Monotone: each status flips `OPEN → CONFIRMED` or `OPEN → DEMOTED`. Silent
retract forbidden. Verifier: `hexa run verify/falsifier_check.hexa` (closure
pct per falsifier across the 3-tier ladder). Detail tables in §B.

- **F-AURA-1** (form factor) — A passive 3.6 g/side mastoid clip with a
  bone-conduction anchor cannot mechanically + thermally host an RT-SC nano-coil
  array coupling through ~5 mm of temporal bone without invasive electrodes or a
  craniotomy. (T1 `calc_clip` · T2 `numerics_clip` · T3 `numerics_clip_parity`
  vs BTE hearing-aid / Shokz bone-conduction / AirPods / eyeglass-arm masses.)
- **F-AURA-2** (coil / channel) — A room-temperature superconducting nano-coil
  tile cannot generate the focal magnetic-field gradient ∂B/∂x needed for
  selective cortical read **and** write at the per-channel SNR a σ²=144-ch tile
  claims, inside the 3.6 g power/thermal budget. (T1 `calc_coil` · T2
  `numerics_coil` · T3 `numerics_coil_parity` vs TMS figure-8 coil / OPM-MEG /
  SQUID-MEG / Neuralink-N1 / Utah-array / Stentrode channel & field data.)
- **F-AURA-3** (cortical I/O) — Non-invasive cortical injection cannot deliver
  the perceptual bandwidth (audio ≈ 2 ch × 20 kHz; vision ≈ 10⁶ "pixels" ×
  60 Hz; haptic ≈ 10⁴ taxels) of the wearables it claims to replace — the
  substituted-device aggregate perceptual throughput exceeds the achievable
  cortical write rate. (T1 `calc_cortex` · T2 `numerics_cortex` · T3
  `numerics_cortex_parity` vs cochlear-implant ch / Argus-II + Orion electrode
  count / BrainGate-handwriting + speech-BCI WPM / Flesher-2016 S1 ICMS touch.)
- **F-AURA-4** (safety / certification) — A continuously-worn behind-the-ear
  field-coil device cannot keep cortical induced current density / RF SAR /
  tissue heating / seizure-induction risk inside ICNIRP-2020 + IEEE-C95.1-2019 +
  IEC-60601-1 + Shannon-1992 charge-density limits at the field strengths
  F-AURA-2/3 require. (T1 `calc_safety` · T2 `numerics_safety` · T3
  `numerics_safety_parity` vs ICNIRP SAR / IEEE C95.1 / Shannon k=1.5,1.85 /
  McCreery / Rossi TMS-seizure-incidence / FDA MRI-conditional labels.)

