| F-AURA-3c  | S1 haptic write cannot reach Flesher-2016 ICMS taxel density → e-skin replacement fails              | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-3d  | aggregate read decode WPM stays below Willett/Metzger-2023 speech-BCI (≈62–78 WPM)                   | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: σ=12 cortical target zones, τ=4 operating modes, 6 pyramidal layers, φ=2 bidirectional,
sopfr=5 ms closed-loop latency, σ·τ=48 K virtual-retina pixels (scales by σ powers per tile count).

### §B.4 F-AURA-4 — safety (current-density / SAR / heating / seizure / no-craniotomy)

Spec: `safety/doc/cortical-safety.md` · Verb: `hexa-aura safety` · T1 `calc_safety` · T2 `numerics_safety` · T3 `numerics_safety_parity`

| ID         | Falsifier                                                                                          | Status |
|------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------|
| F-AURA-4a  | continuous-wear induced charge density exceeds Shannon k≤1.5 (and k≤1.85) cortical damage limit      | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4b  | local 10 g-avg SAR exceeds ICNIRP-2020 / IEEE-C95.1-2019 2 W/kg at F-AURA-2 write field strengths    | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4c  | scalp/cortex steady-state heating exceeds ΔT ≤ 0.5 K (CEM43 thermal-dose) limit                      | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4d  | EEG-watchdog seizure-detection ROC cannot reach the μ=1 → 1 % false-alarm floor at clinical sensitivity | OPEN   |
| F-AURA-4e  | device is not MRI-conditional (RF heating / displacement-force / image-artifact fails IEC 60601 / ASTM F2503) | OPEN   |

n=6 encoding: Shannon k ≤ sopfr/τ ≈ 1.25 → rounded design target ≤ 1.5; SAR ≤ φ = 2 W/kg;
ΔT ≤ φ/τ = 0.5 K; coating lifetime φ·σ = 24 yr; μ=1 → 1 % watchdog false-alarm floor; τ=4-layer biocompatible coating.

